Hello World

0. You need `make' and `gcc' to be installed on system to compile project,
	after that you can install this simple program

1. Compile the program using following command:
	$ make

2. Install the program using following command:
	$ sudo make install
	
3. Clean the temporary files using following command:
	$ sudo make clean

4. Run program using following command, whenever:
	$ hello

!. If you have not `make' installed, compile and install manually as:
	$ gcc -c src/greet.c && \
	  gcc -c src/main.c && \
	  gcc -o bin/hello greet.o main.o

	$ sudo cp -rf bin/hello /usr/bin/ 

	$ rm -rf *.o
	
   Run agin using 4.
